erumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10090139/Vision-Metron-TFW-Disc-lightweight-carbon-TT-wheel_EF-pro-Cycling-Stefan-Bissegger_photo-by-Bettiniphoto_Paris-Nice-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10090139/Vision-Metron-TFW-Disc-lightweight-carbon-TT-wheel_EF-pro-Cycling-Stefan-Bissegger_photo-by-Bettiniphoto_Paris-Nice-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10090139/Vision-Metron-TFW-Disc-lightweight-carbon-TT-wheel_EF-pro-Cycling-Stefan-Bissegger_photo-by-Bettiniphoto_Paris-Nice-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252792\">c. Vision, photo by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/Bettiniphoto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">BettiniPhoto</a></figcaption></figure><p>Tubeless-ready and lightweight are the big buzz words around the new disc TT wheel, but of course aerodynamics, power-transfer stiffness, and ultimate speed were the final goal. Vision’s aerodynamic engineering in the USA refined the profile of the disc, fine-tuning it for drag reduction in the San Diego wind tunnel.</p><p>Vision coats the wheel with an ultralight 4g finish using supposedly unique paint chemistry that actually improves aerodynamics by manipulating boundary layer airflow when the wheel is spinning. The wheel is entirely made in Italy, including alloy hub internals and waterproof Italian hybrid ceramic bearings that spin on specially-coated, aerospace-developed steel races.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10090131/Vision-Metron-TFW-Disc-lightweight-carbon-TT-wheel_prototype-rear-wheel-only.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10090131/Vision-Metron-TFW-Disc-lightweight-carbon-TT-wheel_prototype-rear-wheel-only.jpg\" alt=\"Vision Metron TFW Disc lightweight carbon TT wheel, rim 